{{Other uses|Ittifaq (disambiguation)}} '''The Party of Tatar National Independence ''İttifaq''''' or '''''Ittifak''''' ({{lang-tt|Татар милли бәйсезлек партиясе "Иттифак"|Tatar Milli Bäysezlek Partiäse "İttifaq"}}, {{lang-ru|Тататрская партия национальой независимости "Иттифак"}}) is a political party founded in the [[Tatar ASSR]] in April, 1990, and officially registered on January 3, 1992.<ref name="archive">{{ru icon}} [http://guides.rusarchives.ru/browse/guidebook.html?bid=23&sid=319930]</ref> Ittifaq was the first non-[[communist]] party in [[Tatarstan]]. It is commonly referred to as a [[Volga Tatars|Tatar]] [[nationalism|nationalist]] party. It was named in honour of [[Ittifaq al-Muslimin]], a pre-revolutionary Muslim political party represented in the parliament (Duma) of the czarist [[Russia]].
The aims, as claimed by the party, are: * revival of the [[Tatar people|Tatar nation]] * restoring Tatar [[Sovereign state|statehood]] * recognition of the Tatar state as an international entity.
The permanent leader of the Ittifaq party is [[Fäwziä Bäyräm]]ova. She has been leading the party for more than 20 years. The party published its own newspaper - ''Altın Urda'' - from 1993 to 1998.<ref name="TES">{{TES|Татар милли бәйсезлек партиясе "Иттифак"}}</ref>
