WhyEurope is a non-partisan and independent non-profit organization, which was founded in 2016 in [[Freiburg im Breisgau]], Germany. It aims at highlighting the benefit of the [[European Union]] for an average citizen in their daily lives by adopting an innovative communication style. Since September 2017, WhyEurope e.V. is an officially registered association based in [[Tübingen]], Germany. It has approximately 30 members from over 10 European states.

== Background and History ==
The initiative was founded by the three students Hans-Christoph Schlüter, Benedikt Erasmus Kau and Mirko Moser-Abt. All three shared a concern about the rise of euroscepticism and right-wing-populism.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Badische Zeitung|Title=Facebook-Seite "Whyeurope" ist pro-europäisch und populistisch - Kultur - Badische Zeitung|language=German|URL=http://www.badische-zeitung.de/kultur-sonstige/facebook-seite-whyeurope-ist-pro-europaeisch-und-populistisch--134027863.html|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref> The outcome of the [[Brexit]] referendum was the trigger for them to become active. They decided to publish pictures with simple pro-European messages on [[Facebook]], [[Twitter]] and [[Instagram]].<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=euractiv.com|Title=WhyEurope: ‘Brexit was the trigger. We had to do something’|Date=2017-02-24|language=German|URL=https://www.euractiv.com/section/future-eu/video/whyeurope-brexit-was-the-trigger-we-had-to-do-something/|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref>

== Communication Style ==
WhyEurope has adopted a communication style they refer to as “Positive [[Populism]]”. The founders describe the approach as simple, emotional and personal.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=euractiv.com|Title=Students trial ‘positive populism’ in pro-EU messages|Date=2017-01-20|language=German|URL=https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/news/students-trial-positive-populism-in-pro-eu-messages/|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref> They refrain from including difficult, political or legal terms in their slogans and make their messages as catchy and short as possible. Furthermore, WhyEurope aims to trigger positive emotions by connecting political issues to every-day topics such as love or happiness.<ref>{{cite web|title="Positiver Populismus" – Co-Gründer von WhyEurope im Interview|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.laute-europaeer.de/2017/12/08/whyeurope-interview/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=de-DE|pages=|quote=}}</ref> The initiative aims at pointing out the concrete advantages complex benefits of [[European integration]] have in people's daily lives.<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=Friedrich-Naumann-Stiftung für die Freiheit|Title=Why Europe|language=German|URL=https://www.freiheit.org/why-europe|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref> The founders have repeatedly stated that ''Positive Populism'' is to be seen as a simple and emotional communication style, but sustains a foundation of hard facts and evidence.<ref>{{cite web|title=Why Europe? – Euranet Plus|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.euranetplus.de/2017/03/06/why-europe/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=de-DE|pages=|quote=}}</ref> In contrary to actual ‘negative’ populists, they want to provide factual evidence and explanations for their claims.<ref>{{cite web|title=About {{!}} WhyEurope|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.whyeurope.org/about/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref>

WhyEurope considers Positive Populism an approach to oppose current populist and [[Extremism|extremist]] movements.<ref>{{cite web|title=CONTENT: Pourquoi l’Europe? Initiation au populisme positif – Master Europe|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://mastereurope.eu/content-whyeurope-populismepositif/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref> According to them, the technical communication of the European Union might have contributed to the lack of support those institutions have received during the past years. Adopting a more appealing communication approach might help the Union to regain confidence.<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Anne Havenith|Title=Kármán Hochschulzeitung - WhyEurope – Die EU retten mit Social Media?|language=German|URL=http://www.karman-aachen.de/archiv/item/1415-whyeurope-%E2%80%93-die-eu-retten-mit-social-media|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref>

== Independence ==
Since their foundation, WhyEurope has always emphasized their character as a non-partisan and independent initiative. Despite being in contact with actors of the European Union, they have repeatedly stated their distance to the EU institutions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hans-Christoph Schlüter - Raising emotional engagement with Europe - EuropCom 2017|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HXgi2tmUbls|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=European Committee of the Regions|date=2017-11-10|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref> They refuse to accept any financial support in any form from the European Union and other political institutions or actors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whyeurope.org/support-us/|title=Support Us {{!}} WhyEurope|website=www.whyeurope.org|access-date=2018-03-26}}</ref>

== Relationship to other initiatives ==
WhyEurope has had a number of cooperations with other pro-European initiatives. Since beginning of 2016, Benedikt Kau and Hans-Christoph Schlüter were in contact with [[:de:Daniel Röder|Daniel Röder]] and Sabine Röder when they launched the demonstrations under the name [[Pulse of Europe]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Why Europe – Wahres mit Augenzwinkern – #PulseofEurope|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://pulseofeurope.eu/de/why-europe-wahres-mit-augenzwinkern/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=de-DE|pages=|quote=}}</ref> Pulse of Europe adopted the campaign and the slogan of the campaign “Blijf bij ons” focusing on the [[:de:Parlamentswahl in den Niederlanden 2017|Dutch General elections]]. Together, the initiatives mobilized ten thousands of people joining pro-European demonstrations.<ref>{{citation/core|Title=Duitsers demonstreren tegen 'nexit': blijf bij ons!|language=German|URL=https://nos.nl/artikel/2162875-duitsers-demonstreren-tegen-nexit-blijf-bij-ons.html|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref>

Further cooperations included projects with the [[Young European Federalists]] and [[Laute Europäer]]<ref>{{Citation|title=“Positiver Populismus” – Co-Gründer von WhyEurope im Interview|url=https://www.laute-europaeer.de/2017/12/08/whyeurope-interview/|language=de-DE|accessdate=2018-03-26}}</ref>.
== Reception ==
On 31 January, [[Marine Le Pen]] ([[National Front (France)|Front National]]) filed a parliamentary request in the [[European Parliament]] asking about the funding of WhyEurope through the [[European Commission]].<ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=euractiv.com|Title=Le Pen confuses student initiative with ‘EU propaganda’|Date=2017-04-28|language=German|URL=https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/news/le-pen-confuses-student-initiative-with-eu-propaganda/|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref> Commissioner [[Günther Oettinger]], then responsible person for the EU budget, replied that the Commission has not funded WhyEurope in any way and the name were not found within the central accounting system.<ref>{{cite web|title=Answer to a written question - Whyeurope - E-000605/2017|periodical=|publisher=|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getAllAnswers.do?reference=E-2017-000605&language=EN|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>
{{Quote|text=When EURACTIV first discovered the WhyEurope Twitter account a few days ago, we were puzzled by the freshness of the pro-European messages, in stark contrast to the EU’s usually boring official communications.|sign=Georgi Gotev, Senior Editor at [[Euractiv]]|source=}}
November 2017, WhyEurope has been awarded ''European Public Communication Award'' by the [[European Committee of the Regions|European Committee Of The Regions]].<ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Marco Karp|Title="Why Europe" macht Stimmung für Europa|language=German|URL=https://www.zdf.de/nachrichten/heute/why-europe-macht-stimmung-fuer-die-eu-100.html|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=cantaloup.fm|Title=Auszeichnung für Tübinger Student durch die Europäische Union|language=German|URL=http://cantaloup.fm/news/%EF%BB%BF-auszeichnung-fuer-tuebinger-student-durch-die-europaeische-union/|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref> The prize was received during the EuroPCom in the hemicycle of the [[European Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Preis für Tübinger Studenten: "WhyEurope" wird von der Europäischen Union ausgezeichnet {{!}} Universität Tübingen|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.uni-tuebingen.de/universitaet/aktuelles-und-publikationen/attempto-online/newsfullview-attempto/article/preis-fuer-tuebinger-studenten-whyeurope-wird-von-der-europaeischen-union-ausgezeichnet.html|deadurl=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=German|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WhyEurope: Populismus für Europa - EURACTIV.de|periodical=|publisher=|url=https://www.euractiv.de/section/europakompakt/news/whyeurope-populismus-fuer-europa/|deadurl=|format=|accessdate=2018-03-10|archiveurl=|archivedate=|last=|date=|year=|month=|day=|language=de-DE|pages=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=euractiv.com|Title=Student's project WhyEurope wins Special Prize for communication|Date=2017-11-13|language=German|URL=https://www.euractiv.com/section/politics/news/students-project-whyeurope-wins-special-prize-for-communication/|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Periodical=https://www.siegerlandkurier.de|Title=Neunkirchener Hans-Christoph Schlüter mit European Public Communication Award ausgezeichnet|Date=2017-11-10|language=German|URL=https://www.siegerlandkurier.de/lokales/neunkirchen/neunkirchener-hans-christoph-schlueter-european-public-communication-award-ausgezeichnet-9267296.html|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Surname1=Badische Zeitung|Title=MENSCHEN - Freiburg - Badische Zeitung|language=German|URL=http://www.badische-zeitung.de/freiburg/menschen-x6ga3flix--144855888.html|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref><ref>{{citation/core|Title=Trois étudiants Strasbourgeois récompensés par l’Union Européenne|language=German|URL=https://www.dna.fr/politique/2017/11/12/trois-etudiants-strasbourgeois-recompenses-par-l-union-europeenne|AccessDate=2018-03-10
}}</ref>

In May 2018, WhyEurope has been awarded the [[:de:Arno-Esch-Preis|Arno-Esch-Preis]] by the Association of Liberal Academics in Germany<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.obermain.de/lokal/lichtenfels/art2414,650339|title=Für Europa mit „Positiven Populismus“|date=2018-05-22|work=obermain.de|access-date=2018-05-23|language=de-DE}}</ref>.

